misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes the correct way to right-shift an array by one is to save the last element, move each element one index to the right from the end toward the start, and then place the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap is evident here. This matches Java’s execution model: assignment overwrites array cells, so iterating from right-to-left prevents overwriting values that are still needed. Saving the last element preserves it before the shift.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None for valid inputs; produces correct shifted array output.
